 There are 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

$
\backslash
binom{n}{2}$
\end_layout

\end_inset

 to choose 2 cells, without replacement and with order in choice being irrelevan
t, that will remain empty.
 Fix an assignment that is as such, has two empty cells, then thhere are
 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

$n!$
\end_layout

\end_inset

 different ways to permute the 
\shape italic
balls 
\shape default
